  @.agents{new Job { make the video on the card play automatically and fill up the view port totally - no gaps or border - log in vfs .agents - and easier to rotate and move the arrow open button somehwere center and different icon like aletter heart } }

  Detailed intent:
  - Video on the (gift) card: autoplay reliably (attributes + ref + onMount play()).
  - Video fills viewport totally: use fixed inset-0 object-cover low z (under canvas particles + letter UI), no rounded, no card borders around the video area.
  - The letter/card surface (profile, message, etc) and holo layers stay as the "card" floating nicely centered over the full video.
  - Update placement wrapper in gift scene (FrutigerScenes) so no max-w-md / px constraining the letter surface positioning.
  - Arrow open button (landscape toggle): 
    * Move it somewhere center (e.g. bottom center of the letter surface).
    * Different icon like "a letter heart" (use 💌 for "open more", ♡ or ↩︎ or ♥ when expanded).
    * Easier to rotate: increase the 3D tilt rotation multiplier (e.g. 14deg -> 20deg) so pointer move gives more visible/ fun rotate response; moving button to center also frees edges for easier drag-to-tilt.
  - Log everything in .agents VFS (job here, history on completion).
  - Only touch Hadacard.tsx, FrutigerScenes.tsx (for wrapper), colocated styles, global if needed for video polish. Build after.

  Outcome feeling: When you land on the gift, the personal video (horsey) immediately and smoothly fills the entire screen as the living background — no little card window, no rounded borders, no padding gaps. The holographic letter UI (sealed or open) floats elegantly in the center on top of it with all the foil magic. Particles dance over the video. Tapping the letter opens it as before. The unfold arrow clasp is now a sweet letter-heart (💌) sitting centered at the bottom for easy reach, and dragging anywhere on the letter (edges free) gives a stronger, more delightful 3D rotate/tilt. All previous deliberate open/landscape letter behaviors preserved.

